                                      <h3 class="highlight header-colorize text-uppercase mb-4"><a href="https://www.marshall.edu/academics/programs/theatre-bfa/">Theatre, B.F.A.</a></h3>
                                          <p class="mb-4 size-18">The School of Theatre at Marshall University prepares students for a wide range of careers in the entertainment industry — whether they’re interested in performance, design or production. From stage technician to performer, there are a variety of professions where graduates can put to use all the skills they’ve developed —creativity, collaboration, communication and problem-solving — all in a real-time environment.</p>
                                            <p class="mb-4 size-18">Located in Huntington, West Virginia, which borders both Ohio and Kentucky, Marshall offers two Bachelor of Fine Arts degree programs in Theatre. Students may choose between the following degree programs:</p>
                                              <p class="mb-4 size-18"><strong>Bachelor of Fine Arts in Performance</strong> – This Theatre B.F.A. program focuses on performance by taking the conservatory approach to actor training. Using 21st-Century practices and tried-and-true trends in actor training, the program helps B.F.A. Theatre Performance majors develop their craft according to current expectations in the American theatre, film and television industries. Guided by faculty of outstanding professional credentials, Marshall University Theatre students are given careful, individual attention as well as shared insight and mentorship in the practical side of the “business.” Students who pursue this theatre degree also get a thorough introduction to — and hands-on experience in — production, from costume and set design to lighting and sound.</p>
                                              <p class="mb-4 size-18"><strong>Bachelor of Fine Arts in Production</strong> – Marshall University’s B.F.A. in Theatre Production provides intense instruction on stage and costume design, lighting and sound, scriptwriting and other aspects of producing shows, also providing opportunities to perform. This B.F.A. theatre program is centered on the belief that the best theatre experiences are based on the collaborative efforts of well-informed theatre artists. Marshall’s production students are presented with a sequential series of courses unique to their chosen discipline. Curricula and carefully crafted production calendars are designed to develop an advanced understanding of the art of theatre, focused study within the discipline and applied production opportunities.</p>
                                              <p class="mb-4 size-18"></p>
                                      <h4 class="header-colorize">Why Study Theatre at Marshall?</h4>
                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">Marshall University’s BFA Theatre programs offer a well-rounded experience that encompasses performance and production training, while providing ample opportunity to tie in studies with other forms of the arts. Students are integrated into the performance program, regularly serving as actors, technicians and designers along with other production opportunities.</p>
